blockquote.para:
I assume you do know what “a++” means in C (otherwise, you should start reading
        C-books), so we just try to reproduce this error in a simple c test
        case:#include <stdio.h>

int main() {
 int i=5;
 i = i++ * ++i;
 printf("The current value of i is %d\n", i);
 return 0;
 }

Let’s have a look at a very simple C program, to show the
        issue:#include <stdio.h>
int main() {   
char *mytext;   
mytext = "Help";   
if (mytext == "Help") {     
printf("This should raise a warning");   
}   
return 0; 
}

Look at this code
        now:#include <stdio.h> 
#include <string.h>
int main() {   
char *mytext;   
mytext = "Help";   
if (strcmp(mytext,"Help")==0) {     
printf("No warning here\n");   
}
return 0; 
}
